1
00:01:00,039 --> 00:01:00,799
Lao Lu.

2
00:01:04,760 --> 00:01:05,760
What's that smell?

3
00:01:07,519 --> 00:01:09,599
A bit sour, but smells pretty good.

4
00:01:15,519 --> 00:01:16,200
Fatty.

5
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:17,920
There's a cobra.

6
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:28,879
You scared me to death.

7
00:01:28,879 --> 00:01:30,599
I've been terrified of snakes since I was a kid.

8
00:01:30,920 --> 00:01:32,040
Look how scared you are.

9
00:01:32,319 --> 00:01:34,480
There wouldn't be cobras in this kind of terrain.

10
00:01:36,560 --> 00:01:37,680
No, Advisor He.

11
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:39,599
Why would you joke about that?

12
00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:41,159
At most, there are pit vipers.

13
00:01:44,519 --> 00:01:45,079
Advisor He.

14
00:01:45,079 --> 00:01:47,120
You're jumping all over the place.

15
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:48,480
Good thing my heart is strong.

16
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:50,280
If it were Lao Lu, he would've fainted by now.

17
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,400
What is it now?

18
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:55,319
I think I got stung by a hornet.

19
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,400
Hornets!

20
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,159
Run!

21
00:02:01,159 --> 00:02:01,799
Hurry!

22
00:02:02,359 --> 00:02:03,239
Go, go, go!

23
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:11,560
Dead end!

24
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:19,840
Flares!

25
00:02:20,919 --> 00:02:22,360
Get your flares out!

26
00:02:22,479 --> 00:02:22,840
Okay!

27
00:02:22,840 --> 00:02:23,879
The ones I gave you yesterday!

28
00:02:23,879 --> 00:02:25,479
Hurry! Where are the flares?

29
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:36,960
Where... where are they?

30
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,120
Lao Lu, I can't see!

31
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:38,680
Here they are!

32
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:39,599
O-Over there!

33
00:02:39,599 --> 00:02:40,639
Over there! Over there!

34
00:03:04,599 --> 00:03:05,319
Did they leave?

35
00:03:05,319 --> 00:03:06,039
It really works.

36
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,319
They're all gone.

37
00:03:20,080 --> 00:03:21,039
Are you guys okay?

38
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,319
We're fine. We're okay.

39
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,879
The ones you just encountered...

40
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:25,199
are Nanyun giant black wasps.

41
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,719
It's a local species of wasp.

42
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:27,919
They are extremely aggressive.

43
00:03:28,319 --> 00:03:29,159
Thank goodness.

44
00:03:29,159 --> 00:03:30,240
Good thing you showed up.

45
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:32,560
Otherwise, we would've been wiped out.

46
00:03:32,680 --> 00:03:33,439
Thanks a lot.

47
00:03:33,439 --> 00:03:34,360
Good thing no one got stung.

48
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,080
Once stung,

49
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:36,199
the venom spreads extremely fast.

50
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:37,719
Locals say

51
00:03:38,199 --> 00:03:39,879
three of them can sting a cow to death.

52
00:03:40,039 --> 00:03:40,919
What about a person?

53
00:03:40,919 --> 00:03:41,759
Just one, probably.

54
00:03:43,199 --> 00:03:45,120
Fatty! Fatty! Fatty!

55
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:45,840
Fatty!

56
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:46,439
What's wrong?

57
00:03:46,439 --> 00:03:47,159
What happened?

58
00:03:50,479 --> 00:03:51,319
My butt...

59
00:03:51,479 --> 00:03:52,159
His butt!

60
00:03:52,439 --> 00:03:53,639
Quick, take off his pants!

61
00:03:54,479 --> 00:03:55,240
Take off his pants!

62
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:57,280
If not treated in time,

63
00:03:57,560 --> 00:03:58,680
he'll be in big trouble.

64
00:04:00,680 --> 00:04:01,719
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

65
00:04:08,719 --> 00:04:09,479
Need any help?

66
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:10,159
No need!

67
00:04:18,439 --> 00:04:19,319
Don't let him move around.

68
00:04:19,319 --> 00:04:20,160
Don't move around.

69
00:04:24,319 --> 00:04:25,040
Don't move.

70
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:26,560
It'll be done in a second.

71
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,959
Okay, almost done.

72
00:04:32,199 --> 00:04:33,040
Done. All good?

73
00:04:33,839 --> 00:04:34,360
Done.

74
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,199
Done.

75
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:36,920
Good thing we treated it in time.

76
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,120
You'll be fine.

77
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,839
Not bad, young man.

78
00:04:39,959 --> 00:04:41,120
You're quite skilled.

79
00:04:41,639 --> 00:04:42,519
This little butterfly...

80
00:04:43,759 --> 00:04:44,439
Thank you.

81
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:45,399
It's really pretty.

82
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:46,879
You forgot.

83
00:04:47,319 --> 00:04:48,519
This is exactly what I study.

84
00:04:49,839 --> 00:04:50,759
Why are you here?

85
00:04:50,759 --> 00:04:51,759
Weren't you waiting for butterflies?

86
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:52,639
No luck.

87
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:54,920
The place I was heading to...

88
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,240
It just rained.

89
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,759
Then where are you going now?

90
00:04:59,959 --> 00:05:00,759
Guyu.

91
00:05:03,079 --> 00:05:04,199
You're going to Guyu too?

92
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:05,439
I've looked into it.

93
00:05:05,879 --> 00:05:07,720
Past Ailong Mountain is Guyu.

94
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:09,079
It's located deep in the mountains.

95
00:05:09,079 --> 00:05:11,000
Swarms of large butterflies often pass through there.

96
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,680
Are you guys going to Guyu too?

97
00:05:18,519 --> 00:05:19,839
Fatty, how are you doing?

98
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:21,399
Much better.

99
00:05:21,519 --> 00:05:23,720
I think we should give him another anti-inflammatory shot.

100
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,120
No, no.

101
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:26,680
I'm fine. All good.

102
00:05:26,759 --> 00:05:28,360
Everyone, everyone.

103
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,360
Everyone.

104
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:31,600
I have some bad news to tell you.

105
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,519
We're here.

106
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:39,160
This is the cave I mentioned before.

107
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:42,720
Originally,

108
00:05:43,079 --> 00:05:44,680
we were supposed to take a bamboo raft from here

109
00:05:44,879 --> 00:05:46,120
and go straight out.

110
00:05:46,439 --> 00:05:47,600
But for some reason,

111
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,319
the water in this river channel has receded too.

112
00:05:49,519 --> 00:05:50,959
We can't use the bamboo raft anymore.

113
00:05:51,079 --> 00:05:52,639
Then think of a way, Brother Liu.

114
00:05:52,639 --> 00:05:53,759
How do we go?

115
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,079
I went in and checked.

116
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:56,399
Just inside,

117
00:05:56,399 --> 00:05:57,319
there's no water.

118
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:58,399
A bit further in,

119
00:05:58,399 --> 00:05:59,240
the water isn't deep either.

120
00:05:59,319 --> 00:06:00,839
We can wade across.

121
00:06:00,839 --> 00:06:02,000
Then let's try walking.

122
00:06:02,879 --> 00:06:03,800
It's our only option.

123
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:05,639
Dawei.

124
00:06:06,639 --> 00:06:08,120
You should come with us.

125
00:06:08,959 --> 00:06:10,040
Adding another person...

126
00:06:10,439 --> 00:06:12,199
shouldn't you get my permission first?

127
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:14,600
Dawei, look.

128
00:06:14,839 --> 00:06:16,519
We already paid anyway.

129
00:06:16,519 --> 00:06:17,600
Fifty per person.

130
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,240
How about you spend a little too?

131
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,800
We can all go together.

132
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:22,720
Fifty RMB?

133
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:23,879
O-Obviously.

134
00:06:24,079 --> 00:06:25,800
Fifty RMB is quite a lot.

135
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,079
Did you expect Foreign Exchange Certificates?

136
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:29,000
I've used up all the money I exchanged.

137
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:30,120
Now I only have Foreign Exchange Certificates.

138
00:06:30,279 --> 00:06:31,240
No RMB.

139
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:32,519
You...

140
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,160
How about I pay Dawei's fifty?

141
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:37,319
Really?

142
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:39,319
You can give the Foreign Exchange Certificates to Shutong later.

143
00:06:40,959 --> 00:06:42,040
Okay, deal.

144
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:44,759
Take the bamboo pole.

145
00:06:45,199 --> 00:06:46,120
Scout the path from behind.

146
00:06:46,959 --> 00:06:47,639
Let's go.

147
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,480
What's wrong?

148
00:07:23,319 --> 00:07:24,319
Alright, alright, let's go.

149
00:07:25,519 --> 00:07:26,519
What the hell are these?

150
00:07:26,839 --> 00:07:28,720
Why are they hanging like hanged men?

151
00:07:28,759 --> 00:07:29,759
Aren't these the same

152
00:07:29,759 --> 00:07:31,240
stone figures we saw on the way?

153
00:07:31,519 --> 00:07:32,680
You saw them too?

154
00:07:33,079 --> 00:07:34,480
It... It was because of this stone figure

155
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,079
suddenly rolling down the mountain

156
00:07:36,319 --> 00:07:37,800
that I fell off the cliff.

157
00:07:40,439 --> 00:07:41,240
Hanged men?

158
00:07:45,560 --> 00:07:46,240
Brother Liu,

159
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:49,920
did you know these things were in here?

160
00:07:50,439 --> 00:07:51,439
I've never heard of them.

161
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:52,199
But,

162
00:07:52,199 --> 00:07:54,040
these kinds of stone figures in our Ailong Mountain

163
00:07:54,079 --> 00:07:54,959
are very common.

164
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,399
As long as you don't touch them,

165
00:07:56,399 --> 00:07:57,639
there shouldn't be any problems.

166
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:04,120
These stone figures must be man-made, right?

167
00:08:04,959 --> 00:08:05,680
If they are man-made,

168
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,279
does it mean

169
00:08:06,279 --> 00:08:08,199
we've entered the area of the Dian King's ruins?

170
00:08:08,959 --> 00:08:10,360
But these aren't made of stone.

171
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,879
Not stone?

172
00:08:12,519 --> 00:08:14,160
Could they be Tianjin clay figurines?

173
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,120
It seems they really are.

174
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:20,360
This is a limestone cave.

175
00:08:22,439 --> 00:08:24,920
Nature's craftsmanship is truly uncanny.

176
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,000
Hey kid,

177
00:08:41,679 --> 00:08:43,679
you've been hanging around with us every day,

178
00:08:43,679 --> 00:08:45,039
how do you know this butterfly

179
00:08:45,039 --> 00:08:46,360
is definitely in this place?

180
00:08:47,879 --> 00:08:50,440
Legend has it that a man named Kashenfu

181
00:08:50,440 --> 00:08:51,759
in a valley in Nanyun,

182
00:08:51,759 --> 00:08:53,000
found this kind of butterfly.

183
00:08:53,320 --> 00:08:54,360
I even have the data here.

184
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,279
Alright, alright.

185
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:57,000
No need to bother taking out your data.

186
00:08:57,279 --> 00:08:59,159
But does your data say

187
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:01,840
this butterfly only appears where there are ruins?

188
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:03,720
Ruins?

189
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,919
What ruins?

190
00:09:08,159 --> 00:09:10,519
Ruins, not bad!

191
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:12,000
By the way,

192
00:09:12,159 --> 00:09:15,120
Sister Yang said you are archaeologists.

193
00:09:15,399 --> 00:09:18,559
If there are ruins in Guyu,

194
00:09:18,559 --> 00:09:20,000
then I've come to the right place.

195
00:09:20,399 --> 00:09:21,080
Alright, alright.

196
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:21,840
Silly kid.

197
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:22,960
He gets so happy mentioning butterflies,

198
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,039
just like a child.

199
00:09:54,639 --> 00:09:55,279
Run!

200
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:56,480
Hurry up!

201
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:02,840
Go, go!

202
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:05,200
Hurry!

203
00:10:05,919 --> 00:10:06,399
Go!

204
00:10:19,159 --> 00:10:20,240
What's going on?

205
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:23,960
Good lord.

206
00:10:25,759 --> 00:10:27,480
We must have triggered a trap.

207
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,879
Why are there traps in this cave?

208
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:30,960
Sorry.

209
00:10:31,399 --> 00:10:33,120
It seems I accidentally

210
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:34,720
stepped on a stone slab just now.

211
00:10:35,399 --> 00:10:36,639
From now on,

212
00:10:36,679 --> 00:10:37,559
without my permission,

213
00:10:37,559 --> 00:10:39,000
no one is allowed to touch anything here.

214
00:10:39,679 --> 00:10:40,919
You found this path.

215
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:42,440
Didn't you know if there were traps?

216
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:43,879
I've never walked this path before.

217
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:44,879
But I know

218
00:10:44,879 --> 00:10:46,120
the herb gatherers around here

219
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,080
all take this route.

220
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:48,759
As long as you don't touch things randomly,

221
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:51,360
I guarantee you can get out safely.

222
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:13,799
Scared me to death.

223
00:11:16,279 --> 00:11:17,840
Since there are stone figures here,

224
00:11:18,480 --> 00:11:19,840
it means there are traces of human activity.

225
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,200
It's not surprising there are traps.

226
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:22,919
But what exactly they are guarding against,

227
00:11:22,919 --> 00:11:23,919
is hard to say right now.

228
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:26,039
Could it be to prevent thieves

229
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:27,080
from entering the ruins?

230
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:29,960
Then we chose the right path.

231
00:11:33,159 --> 00:11:33,960
Commander Chen,

232
00:11:34,559 --> 00:11:37,240
what do you make of these stone figures?

233
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,360
It's highly possible

234
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,519
that this is an ancient burial custom.

235
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,039
Just like mummies,

236
00:11:47,799 --> 00:11:49,039
made from living people.

237
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:54,840
Li... Living people?

238
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,960
Yes, living, breathing people.

239
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:09,159
Look at you. I'm just kidding.

240
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:11,120
Seriously, is that fun for you?

241
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:12,480
Old Chen is right.

242
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,399
In the materials Director Zhu sent over,

243
00:12:14,399 --> 00:12:15,279
it was mentioned.

244
00:12:15,279 --> 00:12:17,200
This should be from the King of Dian period,

245
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:20,360
the ancient, evil, and notorious Teng sorcery of southern Dian.

246
00:12:20,840 --> 00:12:21,879
Teng sorcery?

247
00:12:24,519 --> 00:12:26,240
Haven't you all read the materials?

248
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,080
We did read them.

249
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:32,679
Obviously, Advisor He read them the most carefully.

250
00:12:32,679 --> 00:12:33,960
We didn't even recognize that character.

251
00:12:35,679 --> 00:12:37,759
The King of Dian was a shaman king of the ancient Dian period.

252
00:12:37,879 --> 00:12:38,879
His Teng sorcery

253
00:12:38,919 --> 00:12:40,960
uses the spirits of the dead as a medium.

254
00:12:41,399 --> 00:12:43,639
The methods and processes of creating Teng are highly diverse.

255
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,360
These human effigies in the cave,

256
00:12:45,399 --> 00:12:46,720
their bizarre manner of death,

257
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,720
and the extent of fungal decay,

258
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:49,600
all match the methods of the King of Dian.

259
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,399
They must have been tied up,

260
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:53,759
and forced to swallow a type of Teng pill.

261
00:12:54,279 --> 00:12:55,960
Then, their seven orifices were sealed,

262
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:58,279
and they were hung in this cave with large copper chains,

263
00:12:58,759 --> 00:13:01,000
eventually suffocating to death.

264
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:06,399
Wh- What is a Teng pill?

265
00:13:06,799 --> 00:13:07,919
According to the records,

266
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,840
it's a pill necessary for performing Teng sorcery.

267
00:13:11,399 --> 00:13:12,559
After a living person swallows it,

268
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:15,320
Teng bugs begin to parasitize the body and lay eggs.

269
00:13:15,679 --> 00:13:17,240
In just three to five days,

270
00:13:17,519 --> 00:13:18,840
the eggs will hatch in large numbers.

271
00:13:19,679 --> 00:13:21,000
That's really disgusting.

272
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,159
I... I have to say from the bottom of my heart,

273
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,840
feudal superstition really kills people.

274
00:13:28,639 --> 00:13:29,960
Actually, hearing it like this,

275
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:31,360
it's just like parasites in the human body.

276
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,399
It's the same principle.

277
00:13:32,679 --> 00:13:34,000
The Teng bugs and the human body

278
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,919
are basically in a parasite and host relationship.

279
00:13:37,279 --> 00:13:38,679
That's pretty much what it means.

280
00:13:45,399 --> 00:13:46,240
Hey, listen.

281
00:13:46,919 --> 00:13:47,679
What's that sound?

282
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:50,000
Wait a minute. Don't speak.

283
00:14:11,799 --> 00:14:12,440
Th- Th- This...

284
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:14,399
Why does it sound like a boiling pot?

285
00:14:15,639 --> 00:14:17,639
Bro, what's going on?

286
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:21,000
This must be the clay sealing the seven orifices

287
00:14:21,799 --> 00:14:23,360
melting away after soaking in the water.

288
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,320
According to our previous analysis,

289
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:26,799
once it melts away,

290
00:14:26,799 --> 00:14:28,240
something will definitely come out.

291
00:14:28,639 --> 00:14:29,679
Everyone, be careful.

292
00:14:36,759 --> 00:14:37,799
What's the big deal?

293
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:38,679
Get away!

294
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,440
Don't shoot!

295
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:44,000
How is there someone even more reckless than me?

296
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:44,840
Good lord.

297
00:15:43,759 --> 00:15:45,519
These eggs are hatching too fast.

298
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:46,559
We need to get out of here now.

299
00:15:46,559 --> 00:15:47,840
Whatever you do, don't touch these bugs.

300
00:15:48,039 --> 00:15:48,960
Go, go!

301
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,960
We really should've checked the almanac before heading out.

302
00:15:54,039 --> 00:15:55,200
Haven't seen a single ancient ruin,

303
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,679
but we've seen all this messed up stuff.

304
00:15:56,799 --> 00:15:58,120
These are miasma water stingers.

305
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,840
Even though their bite is vicious,

306
00:16:00,519 --> 00:16:01,159
Bite?

307
00:16:02,399 --> 00:16:03,919
Even though their bite is vicious,

308
00:16:04,039 --> 00:16:05,559
they can only survive in the water.

309
00:16:06,080 --> 00:16:08,039
As long as we don't fall in, we'll be fine.

310
00:16:08,159 --> 00:16:09,080
Lao Lu, hurry up!

311
00:16:09,080 --> 00:16:11,799
Not fall in? How is that possible?

312
00:16:11,799 --> 00:16:13,879
Don't we have to wade through the water?

313
00:16:14,559 --> 00:16:15,240
It's fine.

314
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:17,399
There are stepping stones up ahead.

315
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:18,039
Be careful.

316
00:16:18,039 --> 00:16:19,639
We'll be fine if we cross one by one.

317
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:20,840
Wait a minute.

318
00:16:21,559 --> 00:16:24,159
Are these miasma water stingers eating the stones?

319
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:27,480
They really are.

320
00:16:27,480 --> 00:16:28,159
They're biting them.

321
00:16:28,159 --> 00:16:28,720
They're biting them.

322
00:16:28,720 --> 00:16:30,159
These things are way too smart.

323
00:16:30,240 --> 00:16:31,240
If they eat all the stones,

324
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:32,799
won't we fall in and kick the bucket?

325
00:16:33,600 --> 00:16:35,799
These fish are rotten to the core.

326
00:16:36,639 --> 00:16:37,240
Hey kid,

327
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:38,360
don't you know a lot?

328
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,120
Tell us,

329
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:41,120
are these things fish or bugs?

330
00:16:41,879 --> 00:16:43,639
They should be shallow-water insects.

331
00:16:43,879 --> 00:16:44,679
Bugs?

332
00:16:44,799 --> 00:16:45,840
Bugs are fine, bugs are fine.

333
00:16:45,879 --> 00:16:46,759
No matter what, bugs

334
00:16:46,759 --> 00:16:48,200
can't bite a person to death, right?

335
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:48,960
Fatty,

336
00:16:49,120 --> 00:16:51,320
insects are the most formidable creatures in the world.

337
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:53,840
They have the greatest strength and vitality.

338
00:16:53,919 --> 00:16:55,600
A swarm of bugs can easily bite a person to death.

339
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:57,720
It's just their size that limits them.

340
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:00,960
And miasma water stingers this big...

341
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:02,080
It's my first time seeing them too.

342
00:17:02,320 --> 00:17:04,039
And they've grown such sharp teeth.

343
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:04,759
This... this...

344
00:17:04,759 --> 00:17:05,559
I'm guessing

345
00:17:05,799 --> 00:17:07,559
it has to do with the unique environment here.

346
00:17:07,720 --> 00:17:08,640
It caused them to evolve.

347
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:10,319
Hey, you're just spouting nonsense.

348
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:11,799
How do we get out of here now?

349
00:17:11,799 --> 00:17:13,200
How do we deal with these things?
